From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] branding: remove Chrome/Google marketing strings from UI

Removes or neutralises strings in the Chromium UI that promote Google
services, recommend signing into a Google account, or reference the
Chrome brand. These strings appear in:
  - The profile bubble ("Sign in to Chrome")
  - The NTP ("Get more out of Chrome")
  - Password manager promotion ("Save to Google Account")
  - "Made by Google" footer in some dialogs

Strings are replaced with Fennec-neutral equivalents or removed entirely
where the feature itself is also disabled.

ungoogled-chromium removes most of these already; this patch covers
any that slip through, and adds Fennec-specific replacements for strings
ungoogled-chromium simply deletes (which would show blank UI in our case).

PILLAR: Branding / Privacy
JOURNAL: none

---
 chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd | 16 ++++++++--------
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd b/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd
index e5f6a7b8..9d0e1f2a 100644
--- a/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd
+++ b/chrome/app/chromium_strings.grd
@@ -92,20 +92,20 @@
       <message name="IDS_SIGNIN_PROMO_SIGNIN_BUTTON_TEXT_MD" desc="Sign-in promo button.">
-        Sign in to Chrome
+        Sign in
       </message>

       <message name="IDS_NTP_CUSTOM_BACKGROUND_RESTORE_TOOLTIP" desc="Tooltip to restore NTP background.">
-        Restore the Chrome default background
+        Restore the default background
       </message>

       <message name="IDS_SETTINGS_SYNC_DESCRIPTION" desc="Description of sync feature.">
-        Sync your bookmarks, passwords, and more to your Google Account. Available on all your Chrome devices.
+        Sync your bookmarks and settings. Configure a sync server in Settings → Services.
       </message>

       <message name="IDS_PASSWORDS_GOOGLE_ACCOUNT_LINK_LABEL" desc="Link to manage passwords in Google account.">
-        Manage in your Google Account
+        Manage passwords
       </message>

       <message name="IDS_SAVE_PASSWORD_TO_ACCOUNT" desc="Save password prompt.">
-        Save password to your Google Account?
+        Save this password?
       </message>

       <message name="IDS_CHROME_SIGNIN_PROMPT_FOR_NEW_PROFILE" desc="Sign-in prompt.">
-        Get more out of Chrome
+        Fennec — private by default
       </message>

